01:36:03.243 --> 01:36:06.460
So this is a different technology
also developed in my lab

01:36:06.460 --> 01:36:10.040
here, and it's part of a broader approach

01:36:10.040 --> 01:36:12.280
that we call hydrogel-tissue chemistry.

01:36:12.280 --> 01:36:15.320
And what this is, is it's building a gel,

01:36:15.320 --> 01:36:20.270
like a clear jello-like substance
from within all the cells

01:36:20.270 --> 01:36:24.083
of a tissue or even an
animal, all at once.

01:36:25.192 --> 01:36:26.470
So you're effectively building a gel

01:36:26.470 --> 01:36:28.870
inside all the cells at once.

01:36:28.870 --> 01:36:30.970
Now, that's an odd thing to do.

01:36:30.970 --> 01:36:31.803
Why do we do it?

01:36:31.803 --> 01:36:36.340
Well, we do it to transform the tissue

01:36:36.340 --> 01:36:39.890
into a more tractable accessible object.

01:36:39.890 --> 01:36:43.210
And the reason that works
is having built this gel,

01:36:43.210 --> 01:36:47.170
this new infrastructure inside the tissue,

01:36:47.170 --> 01:36:48.760
we can then use chemical tricks,

01:36:48.760 --> 01:36:51.460
and we can link the
molecules we care about,

01:36:51.460 --> 01:36:55.530
like proteins or RNAs
which are the things,

01:36:55.530 --> 01:36:58.000
as you know, right before
they become proteins,

01:36:58.000 --> 01:37:03.000
we can link them, physically
anchor them to this gel,

01:37:03.070 --> 01:37:04.510
which is a scaffold basically,

01:37:04.510 --> 01:37:08.000
it's an interlocking network of polymers.

01:37:08.000 --> 01:37:10.680
We can link all these
interesting molecules in place,

01:37:10.680 --> 01:37:13.940
lock them in where they were
initially in the tissue,

01:37:13.940 --> 01:37:16.430
in the cell, in all the cells.

01:37:16.430 --> 01:37:18.550
And then we can remove very vigorously,

01:37:18.550 --> 01:37:21.880
everything we don't care about
that's blocking our light,

01:37:21.880 --> 01:37:23.480
that's blocking our molecules,

01:37:23.480 --> 01:37:26.570
coming in to exchange
information with the tissue.

01:37:26.570 --> 01:37:28.980
We can get rid of everything
else, like the lipids,

01:37:28.980 --> 01:37:31.600
the fats, we can
effectively use detergents

01:37:31.600 --> 01:37:34.710
to get them all out,
and then we can see in

01:37:34.710 --> 01:37:37.210
all the things that were
absorbing or scattering light

01:37:37.210 --> 01:37:38.850
are gone, you can have a brain

01:37:38.850 --> 01:37:40.810
that's completely transparent,

01:37:40.810 --> 01:37:42.970
and yet, all the interesting
molecules are still locked

01:37:42.970 --> 01:37:45.910
into place there, at the
cellular and sub cellular level.

01:37:45.910 --> 01:37:47.650
And so this is hydrogel-tissue chemistry.

01:37:47.650 --> 01:37:50.760
The first form we described
was called clarity.

01:37:50.760 --> 01:37:52.480
We use that quite a bit still,

01:37:52.480 --> 01:37:54.280
but there are many variants now,

01:37:54.280 --> 01:37:56.950
that we and others have
developed on this basic concept

01:37:56.950 --> 01:37:59.040
of building this gel within the tissue

01:37:59.040 --> 01:38:00.590
and anchoring molecules into place.

01:38:00.590 --> 01:38:02.170
